<DOC><DOCNO> AP890622-0335 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-89 2044EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f AM-UAWSalaries     06-22 0248</FIRST><SECOND>AM-UAW Salaries,0257</SECOND><HEAD>With AM-UAW Convention</HEAD><HEAD>Bieber Making $91,469 Plus COLA This Year</HEAD><DATELINE>ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 3 percent raise for United Auto Workersunion President Owen Bieber and the union's other top officers wasapproved Thursday by delegates to the union's constitutionalconvention.   The raise, retroactive to June 1, boosted Bieber's annual salaryas head of the 1 million-member union to $91,469.42.   Bieber and the other officers also will receive quarterlycost-of-living adjustments and 3 percent lump-sum payments on June1, 1990 and on the same day in 1991. For Bieber, each lump-sumpayment works out to at least $2,744.08.   The formula of a 3 percent raise, COLA adjustments and lump-sumpayments for the union's 21 top officers is the same as thatnegotiated for UAW members in 1987 at General Motors Corp. and FordMotor Co. Last year, the UAW negotiated a contract with ChryslerCorp. calling for two 3 percent lump sum payments that brought wagesfor all Big Three workers into balance.   UAW Secretary-Treasurer Bill Casstevens' salary went to$83,078.35 with two annual lump-sum payments of at least $2,492.35.   Salaries for vice presidents Stephen Yokich, Ernie Lofton, StanMarshall and Odessa Kommer rose to $79,800.56 a year, plus twoannual payments of at least $2,394.02. Pay for the union's 15regional directors rose to $71,409.48 with lump sum payments of atleast $2,142.28.   The salary increases came as delegates to the convention, whichconcludes Friday, approved a report from the constitution committee.</TEXT></DOC>